The paper deals with the construction of Cover Free Families, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DM). However, the paper also mentions applications in theoretical computer science, such as in parameterized algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to categories such as cs.CC (computational complexity) and cs.IT (information theory). The construction of these families also involves algorithms and data structures, which could place it in categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CG (computational geometry).
